From 4f32d91c941f3c6a3d9055bf934a3fa20ba24f16 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>
Date: Fri, 15 May 2026 13:21:28 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] fix(stack): peft dep + cookie hydration + model UX + Enter
 key
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit
ingestion / deps
- requirements.backend: pin peft (FlagEmbedding 1.2's flag_reranker
  imports it unconditionally even when no reranker is loaded — without
  it BGE-M3 init explodes with ModuleNotFoundError).
session
- frontend/session.py: serialize cookie value as JSON (dict round-trip
  via extra-streamlit-components was producing '[object Object]' on
  some browsers) and add a short rerun-retry loop so the iframe gets a
  few hundred ms to push browser cookies into Python before we conclude
  there is no session. Fixes 'logged out on refresh'.
model selection
- services/llm: list_pulled_models() reads /api/tags from Ollama;
  pull_model() streams /api/pull progress so the UI can show it.
- backend /chat/models now returns {available, pullable, default}
  where 'available' is what's actually loaded in Ollama and 'pullable'
  is configured-but-missing.
- POST /chat/models/pull triggers a pull (instructor only) and streams
  Ollama's progress events back as NDJSON.
- Frontend sidebar: dropdown shows only pulled models; a "Download
  more models" expander lets instructors pull missing ones with a
  live progress display, then auto-refreshes the list.
login UX
- frontend/styles.py: bind_login_enter() injects a one-shot JS that
  attaches a keydown listener to every password input. Pressing Enter
  finds the form's primary submit button and clicks it explicitly,
  working around Streamlit 1.57's form-submit drop when iframe widgets
  are on the page. Idempotent via a data-attribute guard.
- frontend/app.py calls bind_login_enter() at the bottom of the auth
  page so the listener is installed every time the form is rendered.
